                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.846,
                                "byte_start": 77824,
                                "byte_stop": 113246,
                                "text": "The disposition in number 72-617, Gertz against Welch will be announced by Mr. Justice Powell."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.846,
                        "stop": 177.937,
                        "byte_start": 113246,
                        "byte_stop": 789608,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15119,
                            "name": "Lewis F. Powell, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/lewis_f_powell_jr",
                            "last_name": "Powell",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2764,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 63612000,
                                    "date_end": 551682000,
                                    "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2764"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32738,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 53543,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/lewis_f_powell_jr.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 5649,
                            "identifier": "lewis_f_powell_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.846,
                                "stop": 15.962,
                                "byte_start": 113246,
                                "byte_stop": 141772,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari from the United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.962,
                                "stop": 27.302,
                                "byte_start": 141772,
                                "byte_stop": 187120,
                                "text": "It involves a libel action by a reputable attorney against a magazine that\u2019s falsely libeled him of Leninist and a communist fronter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 27.302,
                                "stop": 35.83,
                                "byte_start": 187120,
                                "byte_stop": 221184,
                                "text": "The district court denying recovery, held that the subject of the magazine article was a matter of public interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.83,
                                "stop": 45.226,
                                "byte_start": 221184,
                                "byte_stop": 258800,
                                "text": "The court therefore applied the strict standard of New York Times against Sullivan, a case decided here in 1964."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.226,
                                "stop": 47.761,
                                "byte_start": 258800,
                                "byte_stop": 268936,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 47.761,
                                "stop": 66.928,
                                "byte_start": 268936,
                                "byte_stop": 345631,
                                "text": "In the New York Times case, this Court held for the first time that where a public official was a plaintiff in a libel case, it was necessary for him to prove knowledge of falsity or reckless disregard of truth."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.928,
                                "stop": 77.099,
                                "byte_start": 345631,
                                "byte_stop": 386278,
                                "text": "The New York Times standard subsequently was extended to apply it to public figures as well as public officials."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.099,
                                "stop": 84.012,
                                "byte_start": 386278,
                                "byte_stop": 413968,
                                "text": "The rationale of this line of cases is grounded of course in the First Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.012,
                                "stop": 101.475,
                                "byte_start": 413968,
                                "byte_stop": 483767,
                                "text": "We decline today to extend New York Times to a case where neither a public official nor a public figure is a plaintiff, merely because the publication is thought to be a matter of public interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.475,
                                "stop": 113.424,
                                "byte_start": 483767,
                                "byte_stop": 531623,
                                "text": "We recognize the state\u2019s interest in protecting the reputation of private individuals must be balanced against the First Amendment interest."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.424,
                                "stop": 131.151,
                                "byte_start": 531623,
                                "byte_stop": 602467,
                                "text": "Accordingly we hold that the states may allow compensatory damages, for libel which causes injury to the reputation of private individuals without applying the strict New York Times test."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.151,
                                "stop": 140.328,
                                "byte_start": 602467,
                                "byte_stop": 639143,
                                "text": "But we would not approve the imposition of liability without fault as we think this would unduly burden a free press."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.328,
                                "stop": 155.462,
                                "byte_start": 639143,
                                "byte_stop": 699747,
                                "text": "Thus with regard to libel suits by private individuals, the states will be free to apply any standard which does not impose liability without fault, such as of negligence standard."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.462,
                                "stop": 162.26,
                                "byte_start": 699747,
                                "byte_stop": 726915,
                                "text": "Accordingly we reverse the judgment of the Court of Appeals and remand the case for a new trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 162.26,
                                "stop": 166.165,
                                "byte_start": 726915,
                                "byte_stop": 742588,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Blackmun has filed a concurring opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.165,
                                "stop": 177.937,
                                "byte_start": 742588,
                                "byte_stop": 789608,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice, Mr. Justice Douglas, Mr. Justice Brennan and Mr. Justice White each has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
